Brain SPECT, CT and EEG in 45 cases of epilepsy during the intermission. The regional cerebral blood flows (rCBF) in 45 cases of epilepsy during the interictal period were determined with brain SPECT. The results were compared those obtained with CT scans and EEG. 48.89% of the SPECT were found to be abnormal while 8.98% were suspected to be abnormal the 35.71% of the CT scans were found to be abnormal